  "prompt": "Do consulting firms show their consultants' transcripts to their clients?",
  "response": "Consulting firms typically do not show their consultants' academic transcripts to clients. Client relationships are generally focused on the expertise, skills, and value that the consultants can provide rather than their academic backgrounds. While firms may highlight the credentials and experience of their team members, they usually do so through resumes, bios, or case studies that summarize relevant qualifications and experience rather than sharing detailed transcripts.",
